It will therefore be interesting, and important for the due estimation of our author, to examine in detail the imitatione of and allusione to Menander in his plays, which can be now ascertained. With this view I shall place before the reader those fragments of the several plays of Menander which have apparently been imitated by Terence. After such a state- ment of details we shall be prepared to go on to some more general remarks upon the relation of Terence to his Greek originale.
